# VERIFICATION MATRIX
SRS Requirements → Verification Method → Test Case → Evidence

1. Verification Method Legend

Method	Description
A	Analysis (static review of logic, math, or structure)
I	Inspection (manual review of code or memory)
T	Test (execution of code under controlled conditions)
D	Demonstration (observing behavior in runtime environment)
⭐ 2. Full Verification Matrix
Requirement (FR‑x)	Verification Method	Test Case(s)	Verification Evidence
FR‑1 — Mode‑Based Dispatch	I, T	TC‑1, TC‑2	Code shows correct branching; tests confirm skip and fast‑path behavior
FR‑2 — Multi‑Pass Rendering	I, T	TC‑3	Four calls to s9() observed; coordinate rewrites validated
FR‑3 — Delta Computation	A, T	TC‑4	dx/dy computed exactly as d0603b - d06037 and d06039 - d06035
FR‑4 — Bresenham Initialization	A, I, T	TC‑5	Step increments and error term match expected Bresenham setup
FR‑5 — Pixel Iteration Count	T	TC‑6	s7() called exactly d06024 times
FR‑6 — Error‑Driven Step Selection	A, T	TC‑7	Negative/positive bx branches validated; increments match SDD
FR‑7 — Pixel Plotting Logic	I, T	TC‑8	`(old & mask)	AH` verified in memory writes
FR‑8 — Framebuffer Integrity	I, T	TC‑9	Only one byte modified per pixel; no out‑of‑bounds writes

